the electron heat flux\nvary as a function of radial distance and Knudsen number in ways that resemble\nobserved data. We note that this model does not include the effects of kinetic\ninstabilities (which may impose saturation limits when active), so for now its\nregime of applicability is limited to collisionless heat-flux evolution away\nfrom the known instability boundaries in parameter space.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Sep 2021 17:08:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-03"}
