ence. No other field UDGs\nfound in low density environments fall near the red sequence. This finding, in\ncombination with our detection of GALEX NUV flux in nearly half of the UDGs in\nsparse environments, suggest that field UDGs are a population of slowly\nevolving galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Sep 2021 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-05"}
