r in centralized setting to compare it with existing HAR\nclassifiers. The experimental results showed that our proposed new solution\noutperformed state-of-the-art HAR classifiers based on CNNs and RNNs, whiling\nbeing more computationally efficient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Oct 2021 07:43:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 17 Jul 2022 21:03:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 4 Nov 2022 11:32:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-07"}
