e parallel protocols. We find a\nsequential \"success-or-draw\" protocol of universal isometry inversion for $d =\n2$ and $D = 3$, thus whose success probability exponentially improves over\nparallel protocols in the number of calls of the input isometry operation for\nthe said case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Oct 2021 08:33:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jan 2022 12:31:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Feb 2022 10:09:08 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 13 Mar 2023 08:24:10 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 14 Mar 2023 10:05:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
