ws the best match with our polarimetric\nresults, yielding a dust density of $\\sim$770 kg m$^{\\rm -3}$. Compilation of\nRosetta and our data indicates the dust's reddening with increasing nucleus\ndistance, which may be driven by water-ice sublimation as the dust moves out of\nthe nucleus. We estimate the possible volume fraction of water ice in the\ninitially ejected dust as $\\sim$6 % (i.e. the refractory-to-ice volume ratio of\n$\\sim$14).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Oct 2021 08:43:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-29"}
